<p>There is a lot of options for recording videos,  MIC and sound type, video setting and output source, developers can  select from <a href="http://developer.android.com/reference/android/media/MediaRecorder.html" rel="nofollow">MediaRecorder</a> class and <a href="http://developer.android.com/guide/topics/media/camera.html#capture-video" rel="nofollow">camera</a> configuration. Some of them work fine on some phone but didn't on others (crash).</p>  <p>How will I know which configuration are working for each type of phone?</p>  <p>For example, some <code>setVideoEncodingBitRate = 120</code> and <code>setAudioEncodingBitRate = 200</code> are working on Samsung S3 but crash on some HTC models.</p>  <p>Option like:</p>  <pre><code>setAudioEncoder setAudioEncodingBitRate setAudioSamplingRate setAudioSource setCaptureRate setOutputFormat setVideoEncode setVideoEncodingBitRate setVideoSize </code></pre>